<br>
Exactly.<br>
<br>
Back in the old days it was all about game play.  I'm sure it was due to limits they could do visually.<br>
<br>
It was a big step from 2D to 3D.  I can't think of another giant step like that one they can do anytime soon.  Yes, they can improve on little details like wind blowing through grass, realistic smoke, hair, fur...etc., but I don't think it's such a big deal anymore.  <br>
<br>
I really hope game makers start to realize that eye candy is not enough to sell games anymore.  <br>
